Follow the steps via clojureX:
http://github.com/citizen428/ClojureX

Essentially, git clone git://github.com/citizen428/ClojureX.git
cd ClojureX
bin/create_symlink

Tokyo-cabinet install:
http://1978th.net/tokyocabinet/
http://1978th.net/tokyocabinet/spex-en.html#installation

apt-cache policy libbz2-dev bzip2 zlib1g zlib1g-dev gcc

sudo apt-get install zlib1g
sudo apt-get install zlib1g-dev
sudo apt-get install bzip2
sudo apt-get install libbz2-dev (This seems to be the standard unmet dependency when trying to configure)

Download the java dependencies:
http://www.1978th.net/tokyocabinet/javapkg/

./configure
make
sudo make install

http://1978th.net/tokyocabinet/javadoc/

Add the following to the ~/.bash_profile:
"
CLASSPATH="$CLASSPATH:/usr/local/lib/tokyocabinet.jar"
LD_LIBRARY_PATH="$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:/usr/local/lib"
export CLASSPATH LD_LIBRARY_PATH
The above settings can be specified by options of the runtime command.

java -cp tokyocabinet.jar -Djava.library.path=. FooBarBaz ...
"

Compojure requires Leiningen, Leiningen Install:
save the script: http://github.com/technomancy/leiningen/raw/stable/bin/lein
chmod 777 lein
./lein self-install

git clone git://github.com/weavejester/compojure.git
cd compojure
../lein deps
../lein jar


Finally, back to cow-blog:
Add the dependency jars to ClojureX's class path:
echo "compojure/compojure.jar" >> .clojure
echo "rhino1_7R2/js.jar" >> .clojure
echo "blog/admin.clj
> blog/config.clj
> blog/db.clj
> blog/layout.clj
> blog/markdown.clj
> blog/pages.clj
> blog/rss.clj
> blog/server.clj
> blog/test.clj
> blog/tokyocabinet.clj
> blog/util.clj
> " >> .clojure




